###Probabilities

####Gustavo

Gustavo gets to choose if the first card drawn is red. There are $26$ red cards ($13$ diamonds and $13$ hearts) in deck of $52$ cards, so the probability the first card is red is $\maroonD{\dfrac{26}{52}}$.

####Katya

Katya chooses otherwise, so the rest of the probability belongs to her:

$\begin{align}
&1-\maroonD{\dfrac{26}{52}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{26}{52}
\end{align}$

###Probabilities

####Corey

Corey gets to choose if the first flip shows heads. It's a fair coin, so the probability the first flip shows heads is $\maroonD{\dfrac{1}{2}}$.

####Yin

Yin chooses otherwise, so the rest of the probability belongs to her:

$\begin{align}
&1-\maroonD{\dfrac{1}{2}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{2}
\end{align}$
